comments.body:
@joeyaiello I definitely agree in the proper renaming of the zip/msi packages.

@pcgeek86 , I got my Windows Server 2016 GA up and running with PowerShell Alpha10. The PowerShell Remoting part, I got Windows to Linux working. But, Linux to Windows not yet unless I'm still missing something. 

I did open an incident for the Linux to Windows Remoting: Remoting Linux to Windows fail after password #2473 

Also, I found out that Install-Packages Chocolatey won't work in either Windows PowerShell 5.1 or PowerShell Core. I had to use one of the command line example to make it work.

:)
